I think I figured out why ASMR videos don't work for me, because the sound of mouth breathers annoys the crap out of me. Like the egregious wheezing of someone who just won't shut their mouth so they exhale half out of their mouth/half nose.

ASMR sounds are often right on the line of misophonia. Eating sounds, for example. Some get tingles, others get an immediate impulse to flip a table. 

Paper crinkling, rain, or fireplace noises might be more up your alley. Avoid anyone who talks.
